<div class="content">
	<p>The first task in setting up your profile is to set is your profile photos. To set your profile photos, first open up your <a href="#help/creating-profile/viewing-profile">User Profile</a> in the <a href="#apps/profile-viewer">Profile Viewer</a> app and then follow these steps. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-camera"></i>Set Your Profile Photo</h2>
			<p>Your profile photo is the main portrait photo that represents you to yourself and to your friends.  To set your profile photo, start by clicking on your name / icon to open the profile editor.  Then, click on the Set Profile Photo button which is located at the button of your profile photo. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/set-profile-photo.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Set Profile Photo Button"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/set-profile-photo.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Set Profile Photo Button</div>
			</div>

			<p>When you click the set profile photo button, it will open up a select image dialog box for you to select a profile photo. </p>

			<h3>Your Profile Folder</h3>
			<p>In your home directory, a set of standard folders are created when you first create your account.  One of these standard folders, named 'Profile', is intended for you to store your profile images. </p>
			
			<div class="icon-grid figure">
				<div class="directory item">
					<div class="row">
						<div class="icon"><img src="images/icons/folders/profile-empty.svg" /></div>
					</div>
					<div class="row">
						<div class="name">Profile</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p>If you have items stored in your /Profile folder, then when you select a profile photo, then that folder will be used. If you have no items in your /Profile folder, then it will open to the folder /Shared/Pictures/Avatars, where a set of shared avatar images is provided.</p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/select-profile-photo-dialog.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Select Profile Photo Dialog"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/select-profile-photo-dialog.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Select Profile Photo Dialog</div>
			</div>

			<p>When you select a profile photo, your profile photo at the top of your profile and in the top header bar will be changed to the selected image. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/profile-photo-avatar.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Profile Photo Avatar"><img src="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/profile-photo-avatar.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Profile Photo Avatar</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-image"></i>Set Your Cover Photo</h2>
			<p>In addition to your profile photo, you can set an image header at the top of your profile which is called your "Cover Photo". Your cover photo usually represents something that you are interested in or that you have a relationship with such as where you live or a place that you have a fond association with.  To set your cover photo, click the button to the upper right side of your profile header. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/set-cover-photo-button.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Set Cover Photo Button"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/set-cover-photo-button.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Set Cover Photo Button</div>
			</div>

			<p>When you click the "Set Cover Photo" button, a dialog box will be opened to allow you to choose a cover photo.   If you have a Profile folder containing images, then that folder will be used.  If you do not have any profile images, then the folder /Shared/Pictures/Desktops will be presented for you to select from. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/cover-photo.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Cover Photo"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/creating-profile/setting-profile-photos/cover-photo.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Cover Photo</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>